gomodel:SYNGO_5053  a     owl:Ontology ;
        rdfs:comment      "Rationale: Authors hypothesize that \"The much smaller molecular size and fewer transmembrane segments of TMEM230 in comparison to known neurotransmitter transport proteins indicate that TMEM230 is likely to be a trafficking protein rather than a neurotransmitter transport protein in synaptic vesicles.\"\n\nFigure 4: Cultured mouse midbrain primary neurons were cotransfected with expression vectors encoding VAMP2 fused to eGFP (pEGFP-VAMP2) and a tag-free version of wild-type TMEM230 or each of the TMEM230 mutants. \"Live imaging showed that expression of all four Parkinson's disease-linked mutants led to significantly slower movement of synaptic vesicles, as shown by reduced transport speed, track length and displacement length, in comparison to cells expressing wild-type protein.\". Experimental description: Results, Figure 4 legend: \"Fluorescence images of synaptic vesicles in transfected primary neurons. Cultured mouse midbrain primary neurons were cotransfected with expression vectors encoding VAMP2 fused to eGFP (pEGFP-VAMP2) and a tag-free version of wild-type TMEM230 or each of the TMEM230 mutants (in the pIRES2-ZsGreen1 vector)\"\n\nThe mutant constructs used to demonstrate the phenotype were actually expressing human protein sequences;\n\"Two cDNA clones containing the full-length human TMEM230 coding sequences (RG219820, isoform 1; RG213024, isoform 2) were used as templates for construction of these expression constructs.\"\n\nDoesn't matter in practise; this protein is very strongly conserved. Mouse and human protein sequences are both 120 amino-acids long and protein alignment using uniprot webtool showed only 4 AA differ." ;
        lego:modelstate   "production" ;
        dc:contributor    "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-2286-1587" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-2514-0216" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-4973-5732" ;
        dc:date           "2023-02-21" ;
        dc:title          "SYNGO_BP_5053" ;
        pav:providedBy    "https://syngo.vu.nl" ;
        biolink:in_taxon  "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/NCBITaxon_9606" .

